FT  11 FEB 93 / Glasgow project
SCOTTISH WIDOWS, the life assurance group, has bought two Glasgow buildings
for development as a mixed retail and office project with an estimated value
of about pounds 20m on completion. The buildings were sold by Legal &amp;
General, another life assurance group, for pounds 5.5m. The development will
have seven shops and 25,000 sq ft of offices.
